<b>Subject:</b> Re: The Woes of the shield<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/the_rathe.cgi?read=70" TARGET=_self>The Woes of the shield</A> (ZamZan)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> Is there anyway to tell if you can use an

<BR>&gt; item before you buy it? This past Sat. I
<BR>&gt; invested in a large wooden shield only to
<BR>&gt; discover my Troll Warrior could not use one.
<BR>&gt; I was using a one handed weapon but was
<BR>&gt; getting my race/class can not use it. At a
<BR>&gt; 50% value loss to sell back, is there a
<BR>&gt; better way to do this?
<P>mez had prublem befur. duren faz foor. mez yoos big ax to barsh 'til mez yoos luts ov barshn toolz.
<P>Bazlaab
<BR>Troll Warrior
<P>**NOTE**
<BR>for those who cant speak the lovely language of troll, i will translate:
<P>During phase 4 I encountered the problem where I bought a large wooden shield and still had the problem. I documented the case with a /bug report. and decided to use the lovely 2- handed axe. Once I was a proper skill level (( 12 or 15 i think)) i began to dual wield. in both cases a big weapon plus a size 20 boot to the head, makes short work on most creatures.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
